Patient: What types of food should I be eating to help my heart?

Healthcare Educator: Eat lots of fruits, vegetables, whole grains and lean proteins like chicken or fish.

Patient: Are there any foods I should avoid? 

Healthcare Educator: Yes, avoid salty and fried foods. They can increase blood pressure and make your heart work harder.

Patient: What about drinks? 

Healthcare Educator: Water is best. Limit drinks with caffeine, sugar and alcohol.

Patient: Can I still enjoy my favorite foods?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, but in moderation. Try to make healthier versions of them.

Patient: How about snacks?

Healthcare Educator: Choose fresh fruits, nuts, and low-fat yogurt. Avoid chips and sweets.